      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> We should also set *mod to NULL here.\n\t\t\t\n> Disagree, this macro decrease reference count and free/nullify this pointer if it become zero. We need not do this explicitly.\n\n #ifdef CONFIG_DEBUG_SLAB\n#define POISON(ptr, c, s) do {} while (0)\n#define POISON_PTR(ptr)  ((void)0)\n#else\n#define POISON(ptr, c, s) memset(ptr, c, s)\n#define POISON_PTR(ptr)  (ptr) = (void *)0xdeadbeef\n#endif\n\n #define OBD_FREE(ptr, size)\ndo { \\\n        OBD_FREE_PRE(ptr, size, \"kfreed\"); \\\n        kfree(ptr); \\\n        POISON_PTR(ptr);          \\\n} while(0)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
